Guy Framework gives a basis for build your games on.

It's object oriented and supports many platforms.
Flexible enough to easily add support for new platforms.

It provides:
- Windows management
- Flexible gameloops behaviours
- Easy input access for keyboards, mice, gamepads, touchscreens...
- Many formats file loaders (textures, shaders, audio...)
- Resource management
- 3D audio (only if platform supports it)
- Templated math library (matrices, vectors, quaternions)
- 3D graphics based on OpenGL ES 2.0, and more.

Platforms supported (right now):
- Windows
- Linux
- Blackberry OS 10

